<title>Template Notes</title>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<para>This document demonstrates the DocBook slide deck.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>You can generate it from <filename>src/dbslides.xml</filename> with
<filename>style/dbslides.xpl</filename>. You'll need to configure the XProc processor and
get a copy of the base DocBook stylesheets.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>This presentation is designed to work at a resolution of 1024x768.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>There are graphics for a 1280x1024 version, but I haven't crafted the CSS yet.</para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>

<para>The bits:</para>

<itemizedlist>
<listitem>
<para><code>slides.html</code> is this file.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para><code>css/slides.css</code> controls presentation.</para>
<itemizedlist>
  <listitem>
    <para>Note that the foil/page/header/body/footer nesting is designed to make the footer
          float to the bottom of the page. Changing the order or nesting of those divs may cause
          problems.</para>
  </listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para><code>js/slides.js</code> controls the interactivity.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<para>Suggestions for improvement most welcome.</para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
